two groups of farmers fought a 
gunbattle over land in a remote town in southern mexico and at least 
nine people were killed authorities said 
state officials said eight of the dead were among a group about 
100 campesinos who occupied a 500acre tract in december after 
losing an eightyear legal battle over the land 
the ninth was one of 83 campesinos who together own a 7000acre 
cattle ranch near pijijiapa that includes the disputed land 
the owners tried to run off the occupying peasants according to 
official accounts of sundays clash 490 miles southeast of mexico 
city in chiapas state 
the farmers occupying the land belong to the leftist independent 
center for farm laborers and campesinos while the owners belong to 
the national campesino confederation part of the governing 
institutional revolutionary party 
there is no doubt that the criminal action with the use of 
sophisticated weapons as well as the decision to kill the 
campesinos was generated by the group of property owners gov 
patrocinio gonzalez was quoted as saying in tuesdays editions of 
the mexico city newspaper la jornada 
he said ak47 automatic rifles were used 
campesinos occupying the land had petitioned for about 2500 
acres for expansion of their cooperative farm enrique vazquez a 
leader of the independent center said tuesday 
under the mexican agrarian reform system campesinos may petition 
for the use of privatelyowned land that is not being used 
