<TEXT>
shantytown dwellers who lost loved ones when 
deadly gas from a union carbide plant enveloped the neighborhood in 
1984 say the 470 million settlement the company has agreed to is 
not punishment enough 
we have often been promised money but for us it was more 
important that those who killed our brothers and sisters should be 
hanged said sunil kumar 
the 15yearold kumar lost his parents and five siblings to the 
cloud of methyl isocyanante that escaped from a storage tank in the 
worlds deadliest industrial disaster 
at least 3329 people died from exposure to the gas released from 
a pesticide plant owned by the danbury connbased companys indian 
subsidiary 
the government says at least 20000 survivors still suffer 
shortness of breath eye problems and other ailments 
on tuesday the supreme court of india ended four years of legal 
wrangling and ordered union carbide to pay the 470 million in 
compensation 
the settlement was acceptable to both the company and india 
which had sought 3 billion 
today the court agreed to advance the date of payment from march 
31 to march 23 and to allow the companys indian subsidiary to pay 
45 million of the settlement with the parent company responsible 
for the remaining 425 million 
the news was slow to sink in at the jai prakash nagar shantytown 
across the road from the deserted union carbide plant which closed 
after the dec 3 1984 gas leak 
kumar still lives with a younger brother in the shack where his 
family slept as the white killing vapor wafted across the teeming 
squatter settlement 
this morning he was studying for high school examinations one 
of the few teenagers in the shantytown who can afford not to work 
he achieved this relative affluence soon after the disaster when 
the indian government gave nextofkin 10000 rupees then worth 
833 for each gas death in the family kumar received 70000 rupees 
throughout the shantytown today many people seemed unable to 
comprehend what the settlement would mean for them 
one man shanker lal said there had been promises of money in 
