a court will deliver a verdict may 20 after 
nearly two years of trying 38 people charged with preparing or 
selling oil blamed for the deaths of more than 700 people an 
attorney said wednesday 
most of the rapeseed oil made from the rape plant of the mustard 
family was imported from france and sold by itinerant merchants in 
1981 in 13gallon plastic jugs around madrid 
people were told it was cutrate olive oil but it was actually 
rapeseed oil processed for industrial use not human consumption 
the trial began march 30 1987 and arguments ended june 28 
1988 an estimated 23000 people say they suffered lasting 
impairments from consuming the oil 
prosecutor eduardo fungairino is asking for conviction of the 
eight principal defendants on charges of involuntary manslaughter 
he is seeking convictions for the other 30 defendants charged with a 
variety of fraud and publichealth crimes 
he also has asked for compensation of 120000 for each of the 
families of the dead 
defense attorneys say prosecutors have failed to show the oil 
caused the deaths and impairments 
