<DOCNO> AP890215-0112 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
top government and communist party leaders paid 
lavish tribute wednesday to the late panchen lama who used his 
influence as tibetan buddhisms no 2 leader to support chinese rule 
in tibet 
party general secretary zhao ziyang premier li peng and other 
top officials stood with bowed heads in front of a portrait of the 
panchen lama capping the official transformation of him in death 
into a national hero and symbol of ethnic unity 
the panchen lama took a clearcut stand of patriotism for 
decades particularly in the fight against the separatists on the 
tibetan issue vice president wan li said in eulogy to about 1000 
government and religious leaders at the great hall of the people 
it is rare for a dead official even one of high rank to be 
honored with such a lavish memorial at the great hall 
the panchen lama died jan 28 at age 50 of a heart attack he was 
a vice chairman of the national peoples congress chinas 
legislature as well as the highestranking tibetan buddhist monk in 
china the dalai lama the faiths top leader has lived in exile in 
india since a failed 1959 tibetan revolt against china 
his death means the loss of a great patriot and statesman to 
our country a devoted friend to our party and an outstanding 
patriotic religious leader to the tibetan people the official 
xinhua news agency quoted wan as saying 
the memorial parts of which were shown on tv was closed to 
foreign reporters reporters also have been barred from attending 
ongoing mourning services for the panchen lama in tibet 
tibetan officials tightly restrict foreigners access to tibet 
for fear they will witness demonstrations of antichinese sentiment 
periodically reported by travelers 
after nearly 40 years of communist rule in tibet china remains 
in tenuous control of the tibetan people despite a heavy military 
presence revolts have broken out sporadically three largescale 
protests and many smaller ones have been held in the capital lhasa 
in the past 1 years 
many tibetans argue that they have their own language culture 
and religion and wish to be left alone 
the panchen lama by virtue of his religious role was the only 
tibetan who supported chinese rule and still held the respect of the 
people he was regarded as the 10th incarnation of the buddhist god 
amitabha 
his death leaves the government without a credible foil to the 
dalai lama who has sharply criticized the chinese for human rights 
abuses in tibet 
the only other tibetan with a high post in the chinese government 
is ngapoi ngawang jigme 78 also a congress vice chairman he was 
an aristocrat and official in the precommunist tibetan government 
who declared allegiance to the chinese soon after their troops 
entered tibet in 1950 he has no strong following among tibetans 
although he has opposed calls for tibetan independence the 
panchen lama spoke out several times against what he considered 
harsh treatment of his people in one of his last speeches he said 
tibetans had paid too high a price for their development under 
chinese rule and that communist mistakes outnumbered their 
successes in tibet 
the comments were reported in the official media at the time but 
have not been mentioned since his death instead the panchen lama 
has been turned into a symbol of loyalty to the chinese motherland 
the party newspaper the peoples daily carried a fullpage 
tribute to him wednesday referring to him as the great panchen 
