eastern europe for pope john paul ii janku complained of attacks 
on czechoslovakia in vatican radio programs navarro said 
he said the holy see confirmed its desire of arriving with 
czechoslovak authorities at a correct dialogue made with good will 
toward resolving the problems regarding the catholic church and in 
particular the nominations of bishops 
navarro said the two sides agreed the radio should keep its 
broadcasts about czechoslovakia in harmony with the holy sees 
attitudes toward that country 
