here are the main points of the 
agreement signed tuesday by the presidents of nicaragua el 
salvador honduras costa rica and guatemala 
nicaragua said it would 
hold national and local elections 10 months early by feb 25 
1990 
give opposition parties equal access to the sandinistarun 
radio and television 
invite international observers to be present during the 
campaign and the election 
free people classified as political prisoners by the 
international commission on human rights 
the five presidents jointly 
agreed to devise a plan within 90 days to demobilize the 
nicaraguan rebels and relocate the estimated 11000 contra fighters 
in honduran base camps 
decided to continue talks on having the united nations send 
unarmed military observers to central america to monitor security 
issues 
the accord does not 
say what will happen if the contras refuse repatriation or 
relocation 
say when nicaragua will free political prisoners 
say whether early elections in nicaragua mean the presidential 
inauguration now scheduled for january 1991 will also be advanced 
