westinghouse electric corp and abb asea brown 
boveri ltd of switzerland are going ahead with planned joint 
ventures following a proposed settlement of a federal antitrust 
action 
the justice department filed both the antitrust lawsuit and 
proposed settlement tuesday at federal court in manhattan 
westinghouse and abb later announced they have established joint 
ventures in the electrical transmission and distribution equipment 
markets of the united states brazil and argentina 
the justice department had sued to block the ventures proposed 
last april claiming they posed significant threats to competition 
in us markets for power transformers converter transformers 
steam turbine generator equipment and services 
in january charles f rule assistant attorney general in charge 
of the antitrust division said reduced competition would likely 
mean higher electric rates for all users of electricity and higher 
prices for many products manufactured using electricity 
under the proposed settlement the justice department withdrew 
its objections to the joint ventures in return for abbs agreement 
to divest its waukesha wis transformer plant and related assets 
one of the joint ventures establishes the westinghouse abb power 
tampd co with westinghouse owning 55 percent and abb 45 percent the 
newly formed company will consist of westinghouse and abbs 
manufacturing plants and engineering and marketing organizations of 
their us transmission and distribution businesses 
under separate agreement abb based in zurich switzerland also 
has acquired 45 percent of the stock of certain westinghouse 
subsidiaries in brazil and argentina 
but as part of the settlement with the justice department 
westinghouse must sell its technology for designing and making 
converter transformers used by electric utilities to convert 
electricity to different voltages for efficient long distance 
transmission 
in its previous objection to the venture the justice department 
claimed the combined power transformer sales of westinghouse and abb 
would exceed 50 percent of total us sales which were more than 
400 million in 1988 
the settlement also bars both concerns from completing their 
previously announced joint venture in the steam turbine generator 
business for 10 years 
westinghouse and abb are two of only four significant sellers of 
major turbine generator repair and related services to us 
utilities along with general electric and utility power corp a 
subsidiary of siemens ag of west germany rule said us sales of 
steam turbine generators and the related services are estimated at 
over 600 million per year 
pittsburghbased westinghouse had 125 billion in sales in 1988 
and employs about 120000 people 
abb asea brown boveri ltd was created jan 1 1988 with the 
merger of asea ab of sweden and bbc brown boveri ltd of 
switzerland abb had 1988 sales of about 18 billion and 180000 
employees worldwide 
combined annual sales of the joint ventures are expected to be 
about 1 billion the operations employ about 10000 and will 
involve 20 westinghouse and three abb facilities in the us and 
latin america 
