shares of chemical new york corp 196 shares of exxon corp with a 
value listed between 5001 and 15000 144 shares of houston 
industries with a value listed between 1001 and 5000 and 330 
shares in trinity petroleum trust with a value listed between 
5001 and 15000 
bakers bank stocks originally were in texas commerce bancshares 
a holding company that grew out of a bank organized by bakers 
grandfather 
in may 1987 texas commerce was merged with a subsidiary of 
chemical and baker became a large holder of the new york 
corporations stock 
state department spokesman charles e redman said last week that 
the white house had undertaken a review of bakers holdings because 
of a more stringent interpretation of government ethics rules based 
on a 1987 justice department opinion 
the office of government ethics interpreting the opinion 
requires officials to be more conservative than previously 
believed necessary by government ethics attorneys redman said 
baker told reporters last week hed not spoken with white house 
ethics chief c boyden gray but that gray raised the subject of 
selling the chemical stocks with robert kimmit a washington lawyer 
recently named as bakers undersecretary of state for political 
affairs 
at that time baker said he would seek a conflictofinterest 
waiver permitting him to participate in decisions affecting the 
economies of developing nations 
but ms tutwiler said baker never asked the white house for the 
waiver 
meanwhile a congressional source speaking on condition he not 
be identified said the senate foreign relations committee asked 
baker last week for more information about his holdings 
the committee had approved bakers nomination for the state 
department post shortly before bushs inauguration 
now that baker has decided to sell his stocks the issue may be 
moot the source said 
